main event: A ground observer in Tallassee, Alabama reported a UFO sighting on November 5, 1957.
interesting points: The object appeared approximately 210 about 10 degrees up and down direction, not touching the ground.
Very little information was provided to evaluate the significance of the observation.
The report does not contain any photographs of the sighting.
The lack of detailed information makes it difficult to determine the nature of the observed object.
The sighting was classified as a D Ground Visual observation.
